{
  "texts": [
    "When the key question is where something is located, saliency maps can provide exactly the information that is needed.",
    "Otherwise, they seem to be of limited use.",
    "AI accuracy.",
    "In AI-focused tasks, saliency maps were often found to be more helpful for incorrect AI predictions (Alipour et al., 2020; Balayn et al., 2022; Folke et al., 2021; Yang et al., 2022).",
    "Similarly, they were helpful to determine that the AI indeed relied on a data artefact but less helpful to determine that it did not (Achtibat et al., 2023)."
  ]
}